Stay Safe Online – Security Checklist for College Students 
(India)
-Use strong and unique passwords
Create complex passwords (minimum 8–12 characters with letters, numbers, and symbols) 
and avoid reusing them across platforms. 
Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)
Activate 2FA on email, social media, academic portals, and financial apps to enhance account 
#security. 
-Exercise caution with links and attachments
Do not click on unsolicited links or download attachments from unknown or unverified 
sources. 
#Protect confidential information
Never share passwords, OTPs, CVV, or personal identification details through calls, 
messages, or emails. 
#UPI/Financial Safety: Keep your UPI PIN strictly confidential
Do not disclose your UPI PIN under any circumstances, even if the request appears to be 
from a bank or official source. 
#UPI/Financial Safety: Verify transaction requests carefully
Review all UPI “collect” requests before approval; remember that receiving money does not 
require entering your PIN. 
# Avoid public Wi-Fi for sensitive transactions
Refrain from accessing banking or making online payments over unsecured or public 
networks. 
#Install applications only from trusted platforms
Download apps exclusively from official stores (e.g., Google Play Store) to minimize 
malware risks. 
#Maintain updated software and security patches
Regularly update your device’s operating system, apps, and antivirus software to address 
vulnerabilities. 
#Ensure secure logouts on shared systems
Always log out from accounts when using shared or public computers to prevent 
unauthorized access. 
Cybercrime Reporting Channels (India):
 National Cyber Crime Portal: https://cybercrime.gov.in
**Helpline Number: 1930**
